==Russian==
===Etymology===
From [[Old Church Slavonic]] {{RUchar|[[сѧ]]}}, the accusative of [[себя]] ([[self]]).

===Reflexive suffix===
'''-ся''' (-sja)

#Suffixed to finite verbs and infinitives to make a [[reflexive]], [[reciprocal]], or [[intransitive]] verb. After a vowel, <u>-ся</u> is contracted to <u>-сь</u>: [[мыть|мыться]] (to [[wash]], ''intransitive''), моется (washes, ''intransitive''), моюсь (I wash, ''intransitive''). When affixed to an infinitive, <u>-ся</u> is pronounced hard as though it were *<u>-са</u>.

